cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about natural language processing and specifically focuses on evaluating the performance of BERT, a popular pre-training model, in capturing structure-dependent agreement relations in multiple languages. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning and deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses natural language processing techniques to analyze and evaluate data, which could also place it in the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category.
